Crisis in A&E has led some to blame a lack of GP appointments for the crisis . 
  Weekend opening hours for GPs has been touted as a solution to relieve pressure on A&Es . 
  David Cameron has promised seven-day access to GP services by 2020 . 
  A number of surgeries in London have been piloting seven day opening . 
  Study found eight per cent drop in attendances at emergency departments . 
  Also found a drop in admissions among elderly patients . 
 